er has lead me down an alternative and rewarding road. I started my formal education in Photography, then shifted to Industrial Design and Advertising. My affinity for writing opened doors for me in business and strategy, which lead me back to business school to focus on marketing and strategy.</p>\r\n<p>You put all those things together and you have a wide array of tools to help you build and manage brands. Most recently I have once again shifted to intense studies in digital strategy and before that fashion design. Always stay in a constant state of learning and growing - otherwise you will lose your competitive edge.</p>\r\n<blockquote class=\"full-width line-2 line-2-after\">\r\n<p>â€œTrends and fads pass, so focus on the deeper meaning of things and the bigger ideas that stand the test of time.â€</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<h3 class=\"question\">Asher:</h3>\r\n<p>Who are your day to day partners at The KDU and SVSV and what are their specific rolls?</p>\r\n<h3 class=\"answer\">David:</h3>\r\n<p>I have some amazing people who surround me and make things happen. Jared Liner is my Creative Director and day to day studio manger partner. He holds the studio together in regards to projects and clients. My wife, Margarita also handles operations and is who I feel most comfortable putting in front of press and sales for SVSV. Josh Vanover, while not based in Brooklyn is a partner who leads the \"art\" side of the army. His work is pushing the cutting edge right now and brings me the most inspiration.</p>\r\n<h3 class=\"question\">Asher:</h3>\r\n<p>You have alot going on at the moment, what are the most recent developments of SVSV?</p>\r\n<h3 class=\"answer\">David:</h3>\r\n<p class=\"spacer\">We are be working hard to expand our in-house factory. We named the factory, Brooklyn Sewn and it has been an amazing and rewarding experience. We are also trying to get back to our roots with more avant garde work to balance the more contemporary work we have been producing lately - the trick is finding the balance between both worlds.</p>\r\n<p><img class=\"full-width\" src=\"http://iandi.spiraldesign.ca/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/svsv-fullwidth1.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<div class=\"caption full-width\">SVSV Our Hyper Reality Collection 2011</div>\r\n<div class=\"three-column line-3-after\">\r\n<h3 class=\"question clear-left\">Asher:</h3>\r\n<p>The KDU is growing daily with new designers, can you tell us about them?</p>\r\n<h3 class=\"answer\">David:</h3>\r\n<p>Each designer, artists or creative professional is hand selected by me personally. People are recommended from other members and colleagues, but the ultimate selection process is determined by me alone. I want the KDU to continue to stand in opposition to mass, technology driven platform and crowd sourcing collectives - the only way to truly avoid this is to know each member personally, having an intimate understanding of their portfolios, work styles and flow.</p>\r\n<h3 class=\"question clear-left\">Asher:</h3>\r\n<p>What are some of the big things coming up for The KDU?</p>\r\n<h3 class=\"answer\">David:</h3>\r\n<p>We have two major book deals which will launch in 2012. I have some big news regarding a merger which can\'t be discussed quite yet, but we have been working on it for some time and will be excited to announce it soon. We will also be relaunching our global network site with new tools for members to communicate and collaborate.</p>\r\n<h3 class=\"question\">Asher:</h3>\r\n<p>Who are some of the people you look up to in the business and design world?</p>\r\n<h3 class=\"answer\">David:</h3>\r\n<p>I am interested in avant garde fashion designers right now. Walter Van Beirendonck has been a big inspiration. I am impressed with the creative vision of my friend Bradford Shellhammer, co-founder at Fab.com.</p>\r\n<p>Jason Denham and Liam Maher at Denham the Jean-maker in Amsterdam never stop amazing me. Joya candles is a Brooklyn, NY based fragrance and object company. I am very impressed with their in-house operation and attention to craft and detail. I\'m also drawn to Kevin Ma, founder of Hypebeast for his attention to detail and curation.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<blockquote class=\"right\">\r\n<p>â€œI was always more interested in what was behind the scenes, than what was on the surface. This curiosity to discover has lead me down an alternative and rewarding road.â€</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n</div>\r\n<h3 class=\"question\">Asher:</h3>\r\n<p>Where are your favorite places to travel/visit?</p>\r\n<h3 class=\"answer\">David:</h3>\r\n<p>I enjoy almost everywhere on earth. I love Iceland most of all and most recently, traveling back and exploring Berks County, PA. I love the speed and Japan, as it clashes with the ancient traditions. I love the beauty of Paris and most of Europe. I am moving towards more extreme traveling as I get older. It\'s more about totally removing myself from other human stimulus and allowing nature to cleanse the palette.</p>\r\n<h3 class=\"question\">Asher:</h3>\r\n<p>As the founder of the Luxury Brand SVSV - What are some of the luxuries in life you enjoy?</p>\r\n<h3 class=\"answer\">David:</h3>\r\n<p>I must admit, I prefer extremely fine cameras. I have been shooting on a Linhof, 4x5 field camera lately and loving it. I typically shoot on Leica\'s and prefer my M9 to anything else. I will be obtaining a 100 year old Graflex RB soon to shoot new portrait studies. Other than that, I prefer nice cars and motorcycles and lots of travel.</p>\r\n<p>I love collecting art, but only things that speak to me personally, so much of my art is from friends or strange things I find in obscure antique stores and flea markets. I typically avoid what many would consider \"traditional\" forms of luxury. I think ultimately, being able to disconnect from work and the chaos of New York and spend time with my wife and family is the best luxury.</p>\r\n<h3 class=\"question\">Asher:</h3>\r\n<p>What\'s would be the best advice you could give someone in the design/entrepreneurial world?</p>\r\n<h3 class=\"answer\">David:</h3>\r\n<p class=\"spacer\">Avoid the hype and drama and focus on the mechanics and building a strong foundation. Education is the best investment you can ever make - so invest heavily in yourself and you will never regret it. Also, trends and fads pass, so focus on the deeper meaning of things and the bigger ideas that stand the test of time.</p>','David Gensler','','publish','closed','closed','','david-gensler','','','2012-04-07 13:20:00','2012-04-07 20:20:00','',0,'http://spiraldesign.ca/?post_type=interview&#038;p=69',0,'interview','',0),(185,2,'2012-03-21 18:42:39','2012-03-22 01:42:39','','david-gensler-svsv1','','inherit','open','open','','david-gensler-svsv1','','','2012-03-21 18:42:39','2012-03-22 01:42:39','',0,'http://iandi.spiraldesign.ca/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/david-gensler-svsv1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(186,2,'2012-03-21 19:13:48','2012-03-22 02:13:48','','svsv-fullwidth1','','inherit','open','open','','svsv-fullwidth1','','','2012-03-21 19:13:48','2012-03-22 02:13:48','',0,'http://iandi.spiraldesign.ca/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/svsv-fullwidth1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(124,1,'2012-03-09 03:58:53','2012-03-09 03:58:53','','Interview-David-Gensler','','inherit','open','open','','interview-david-gensler','','','2012-03-09 03:58:53','2012-03-09 03:58:53','',72,'http://spiraldesign.ca/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/Interview-David-Gensler.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(125,1,'2012-03-09 04:08:12','2012-03-09 04:08:12','','Interview-David-Gensler-3','','inherit','open','open','','interview-david-gensler-3','','','2012-03-09 04:08:12','2012-03-09 04:08:12','',104,'http://spiraldesign.ca/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/Interview-David-Gensler-3.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(70,1,'2012-04-07 13:21:01','2012-04-07 20:21:01','<p><img class=\"right\" src=\"http://iandi.spiraldesign.ca/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/david-gensler-svsv1.jpg\" alt=\"\"