2012-03-05 02:40:56','','asher','','inherit','open','open','','asher-2','','','2012-03-05 02:40:56','2012-03-05 02:40:56','',72,'http://spiraldesign.ca/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/asher1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(102,1,'2012-03-05 02:50:32','2012-03-05 02:50:32','<h3 class=\"question\">Asher:</h3>\r\nHow did you first get into the business of projections and interactivity and how did TMM get founded?\r\n<h3 class=\"answer\">Brodie:</h3>\r\nWe first found an interest in projections in early 2005 during somewhat of the guerilla marketing boom. With our background in film, it was a natural transition to projection advertising. We envisioned projection advertising on a larger scale, not just guerilla but as a clear substitute to billboards.\r\n<p class=\"spacer\">It was about utilizing what was there. Interactivity was something that we almost stumbled upon as an integration into our media services. It\'s now evolved into a full department and technical team here. TMM was founded by myself and Brad Foster, with visions of non-traditional advertising.</p>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"right\" src=\"http://iandi.spiraldesign.ca/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/tmm-feel.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"450\" height=\"299\" />\r\n<h3 class=\"question\">Asher:</h3>\r\nWhat are some of the projects that you are currently working on?\r\n<h3 class=\"answer\">Brodie:</h3>\r\nWe just launched a huge night projection campaign with NBC for the NHL All-Star weekend in multiple US markets in addition to financial sector clients, and some alcohol brands at the moment.\r\n<h3 class=\"question\">Asher:</h3>\r\nHow did you manage to get your hands on the rare Lamborghini Reventon for the exclusive projection mapping event \"<a title=\"The Lamborghini Project\" href=\"http://vimeo.com/33167496\" target=\"_blank\">The Lamborghini Project</a>\"? Did anyone from TMM get the chance to take it for a spin?\r\n<h3 class=\"answer\">Brodie:</h3>\r\n<p class=\"spacer\">This was not a fluke but a rare window of opportunity. We had originally planned to use a white Lamborghini SV, which was sold to a new owner and the Reventon happened to be the backup. I know its wrong for me to say a Reventon was the backup but it was. The project was with SR Auto Group who supplied the Reventon to us. None of us had the chance to drive it unfortunately but the reason behind that is because there are only 20 in the world. It also only had 300 km\'s on it and is really used as an art piece or collectors item.</p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote class=\"full-width line-2 line-2-after\">â€œWork hard, content is king and don\'t accept no, ever!â€</blockquote>\r\n<h3 class=\"question\">Asher:</h3>\r\nWhat are some of the exciting things coming up for TMM in 2012?\r\n<h3 class=\"answer\">Brodie:</h3>\r\nContinuing to push the envelope with projection projects, more interactive campaigns, mapping of buildings, objects, automobiles and of course our interactive windows program.\r\n<h3 class=\"question\">Asher:</h3>\r\nWith offices in Vancouver and Toronto where are you looking to expand to next?\r\n<h3 class=\"answer\">Brodie:</h3>\r\n<p class=\"spacer\">We have a US venture called TMMSB in New York with shipping depots in Chicago and LA which is keeping us pretty maxed right now. Brazil is in the sites as well. We\'re hoping to be set up there for the World Cup and the Olympics in addition to China and potentially London.</p>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"full-width\" src=\"http://iandi.spiraldesign.ca/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/tmm-lamborghini.jpg\" alt=\"\" />\r\n<div class=\"caption full-width\">1 of 20 Lamborghini Reventons in the world</div>\r\n<h3 class=\"question clear-left\">Asher:</h3>\r\nWith clients like Shell and Red Bull, can you see TMM doing something for Formula 1 in the future?\r\n<h3 class=\"answer\">Glen:</h3>\r\n<p class=\"spacer\">Hoping so. Before we started TMM, Brad and I ran a production company focused on automotive filmmaking so we\'re all big car fans here. We had a tent alongside the track for F1 in Montreal this past year and it really changed our lives. Our team was there for a projection mapping installation celebrating Shell Canada\'s 100-year anniversary at the Formula 1 Grand Prix. I can promise that we\'ll continue to push the envelope and work with leading brands to change the media landscape.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"question\">Asher:</h3>\r\nHow did your new creative partnership with Crush Inc. come about and in what ways will this help build The MM brand?\r\n<h3 class=\"answer\">Brodie:</h3>\r\nWe\'re really excited about the creative partnership with Crush. They initially reached out to us as they wanted to work with projection and interactive based mediums and we\'re now able to offer our clients the whole package from creative development to campaign execution.\r\n<h3 class=\"question\">Asher:</h3>\r\nFinally, what\'s your advice to creatives wanting to expand their client base and get their work out there?\r\n<h3 class=\"answer\">Brodie:</h3>\r\nWork hard, content is king and don\'t accept no, ever!','Brodie Gunning','','private','closed','closed','','brodie-gunning','','','2012-04-05 14:47:12','2012-04-05 21:47:12','',0,'http://spiraldesign.ca/?post_type=interview&#038;p=102',0,'interview','',0),(103,1,'2012-03-05 02:51:02','2012-03-05 02:51:02','<h3 class=\"question\">Asher:</h3>\r\nHow did JP logistics start?\r\n<h3 class=\"answer\">George:</h3>\r\nJP Logistics was founded in 1995, the business started as a local auto transport company based out of Los Angeles, CA. We also started the company doing import and export of fine automobiles. After about 9 months of local transportation we had high demand from our customers to transport their vehicles across the Nation.\r\n<p class=\"spacer\">By 1998 we had 7 brand new state of the art trucks traveling the United States and making one customer happy at a time. From there on out we were able to get corporate contracts from Lamborghini, Bentley, Rolls Royce, Bugatti and many many more contracts from the distributors directly. We also have current contracts with major sporting teams and their league offices. I\'m George Sukunyan, the founder and president/CEO of the company.</p>\r\n\r\n<div><img class=\"left\" src=\"http://iandi.spiraldesign.ca/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/jplogistics1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"500\" height=\"380\" /></div>\r\n<h3 class=\"question\">Asher:</h3>\r\nHow many people currently work for JP logistics inc.?\r\n<h3 class=\"answer\">George:</h3>\r\nWe have over 50 employees world wide.\r\n<h3 class=\"question\">Asher:</h3>\r\nObviously you have a personal passion for high performance vehicles, at what age did you decide that the luxury auto industry was the career you wanted to pursue?\r\n<h3 class=\"answer\">George:</h3>\r\nI have been around vehicles all my life. My dad is the biggest influence for vehicles, and now my younger brother Arman Sukunyan who is currently in college is a bigger car nut than both of us. He also learning the art of Logistics to take over company operations after he graduates.\r\n<h3 class=\"question\">Asher:</h3>\r\nWhat are some of your personal vehicles?\r\n<h3 class=\"answer clear-left\">George:</h3>\r\nBeing in the line of work I am, I have previously owned and currently own some heavy metal. From a Lamborghini to a Nissan GTR Hennessey edition # 001. My favorite vehicles are my classics. I have an all original 1957 Chevy Belair, the vehicle only had 2 owners when purchased. I use it as my Sunday beach car during the summer. I also own a 1949 Mercury Custom chopped vehicle built from the ground up by my dad Joe Sukunyan, and our current project is a 1947 Ford COE truck.\r\n<h3 class=\"question\">Asher:</h3>\r\nWhat is your favorite super car and have you had a chance to drive it?\r\n<h3 class=\"answer\">George:</h3>\r\nMy Favorite super car is the ultimate one that every person would love to drive but only some get lucky enough to see it. The Bugatti SuperSport is the ultimate car of choice, I have been fortunate enough not only to drive it but also drive it on the race track. It is just an amazing machine with so much power, control and speed.\r\n<h3 class=\"question clear-left\">Asher:</h3>\r\nHow many locations do you have throughout the world and where are you looking to expand to?\r\n<h3 class=\"answer\">George:</h3>\r\n<p class=\"spacer\">Our import/export division has 6 offices throughout the World and we have 4 offices in Los Angeles. We can also proudly state that we have over 120 sister companies that we have contracts with across the world to use their location for our valuable customer to drop off or pick up their vehicles.</p>\r\n<img class=\"full-width\" src=\"http://iandi.spiraldesign.ca/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/jplogistics2.jpg\" alt=\"\" />\r\n<h3 class=\"question clear-left\">Asher:</h3>\r\nJP logistics inc has a large custom fleet of trucks and trailers, what are some of the special features of these and what helps to ensure safe travel for the vehicles?\r\n<h3 class=\"answer\">George:</h3>\r\n<p class=\"spacer\">All of our equipments have a live GPS tracking system, not only do we track the travel and location but we make sure all of our drivers are well rested, and ready for the great American roads. All of our trucks and trailers are maintained on a daily basis mechanically and physically. We take pride in our equipment as it shows who we are. We have our own in house mechanics at every terminal of ours across the Nation.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"three-column line-3-after\">\r\n<h3 class=\"question\">Asher:</h3>\r\nOn a typical day, how many vehicles does JP Logistics transport?\r\n<h3 class=\"answer\">George:</h3>\r\nOn a daily basis we move anywhere from 15 to 17 vehicles. Annually we book over 4000 plus orders and some orders are 5 to 10 vehicles at a time.\r\n<h3 class=\"question\">Asher:</h3>\r\nThere must be some great perks to this job, what are some of them?\r\n<h3 class=\"answer\">George:</h3>\r\nThe great perks of the job are too many to list, however the best part is being around so many beautiful vehicles. We also have the privilege of meeting some of the greatest people across the world, from governments and celebrities to athletes and Billionaires.\r\n<h3 class=\"question\">Asher:</h3>\r\nWho are some of the people you have had the opportunity to meet?\r\n<h3 class=\"answer\">George:</h3>\r\nI have met the likes of Steve Jobs, President Ronald Reagan, Vladimir Putin, Kobe Bryant, Danica Patrick, Dale Earnhardt (SR &amp; JR), Steve Wynn and Lebron James... the list is endless.\r\n<h3 class=\"question\">Asher:</h3>\r\nThere are some big things coming up for JP Logistics this year, can you share some of them?\r\n<h3 class=\"answer\">George:</h3>\r\nI wish I could, but lets just say we have a very big surprise for our fans and followers. Something that has not been done in the industry. Some of our competitors already have an idea of what it is and they are not liking it.\r\n<h3 class=\"question\">Asher:</h3>\r\nWhat are some of the main things that make your company the best at what it does?\r\n<h3 class=\"answer\">George:</h3>\r\nOur customer service and our personal commitment, from our receptions to our dispatchers and drivers. We make sure that every customer is satisfied. I myself will answer calls and talk to the clients to make sure they are happy from A to Z.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div><img class=\"right\" src=\"http://iandi.spiraldesign.ca/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/jplogistics3.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"500\" height=\"380\" /></div>\r\n<h3 class=\"question\">Asher:</h3>\r\nOut of all of the luxury cars your company gets to transport... what are the ones that still amaze you when you see and hear them?\r\n<h3 class=\"answer\">George:</h3>\r\nBugatti and Koenigsegg\r\n<h3 class=\"question\">Asher:</h3>\r\nAs a CEO of a successful company, what is your favorite part of running JP Logistics Inc.?\r\n<h3 class=\"answer\">George:</h3>\r\nHaving great conversations about vehicles with our customers. From the young kid that has just bought their dream car to the race car drivers that just finished the race and want to share the vehicle performance.\r\n<h3 class=\"question\">Asher:</h3>\r\nLamborghini or Ferrari?\r\n<h3 class=\"answer\">George:</h3>\r\n<p class=\"spacer\">Its a tough one, but I can tell you this... Ferrari for everyday driving and a Lamborghini for the Rally\'s and weekends. I will also say that the new Lamborghini LP700 is my current favorite vehicle between Ferrari and Lamborghini.</p>','George Sukunyan','','private','closed','closed','','george-sukunyan','','','2012-04-05 13:50:26','2012-04-05 20:50:26','',0,'http://spiraldesign.ca/?post_type=interview&#038;p=103',0,'interview','',0),(104,1,'2012-03-12 02:51:47','2012-03-12 09:51:47','<div><img class=\"right\" src=\"http://iandi.spiraldesign.ca/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/interview-image-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"325\" height=\"434\" /></div>\r\n<h3 class=\"question\">Asher:</h3>\r\nWhere did you grow up?\r\n<h3 class=\"answer\">David:</h3>\r\nI was born in Baltimore, Maryland. I lived there until I was in the 4th grade, then moved to Berks County, Pennsylvania. I have lived in California several times in my life, Colorado, Philadelphia and now call Brooklyn, New York home.\r\n<h3 class=\"question\">Asher:</h3>\r\nHow did you first get into design and business?\r\n<h3 class=\"answer\">David:</h3>\r\nI was always more interested in what was behind the scenes, than what was on the surface. This curiosity to discover has lead me down an alternative and rewarding road. I started my formal education in Photography, then shifted to Industrial Design and Advertising. My affinity for writing opened doors for me in business and strategy, which lead me back to business school to focus on marketing and strategy. You put all those things together and you have a wide array of tools to help you build and manage brands. Most recently I have once again shifted to intense studies in digital strategy and before that fashion design. Always stay in a constant state of learning and growing - otherwise you will lose your competitive edge.\r\n<blockquote class=\"right\">â€œI was always more interested in what was behind the scenes, than what was on the surface.â€</blockquote>\r\n<h3 class=\"question\">Asher:</h3>\r\nWho are your day to day partners at The KDU and SVSV and what are their specific rolls?\r\n<h3 class=\"answer\">David:</h3>\r\nI have some amazing people who surround me and make things happen. Jared Liner is my Creative Director and day to day studio manger partner. He holds the studio together in regards to projects and clients. My wife, Margarita also handles operations and is who I feel most comfortable putting in front of press and sales for SVSV. Josh Vanover, while not based in Brooklyn is a partner who leads the â€œartâ€ side of the army. His work is pushing the cutting edge right now and brings me the most inspiration.\r\n<div><img class=\"left\" src=\"http://iandi.spiraldesign.ca/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/interview-image-2.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></div>\r\n<h3 class=\"question\">Asher:</h3>\r\nYou have so many things going on at the moment, what are the most recent developments of SVSV?\r\n<h3 class=\"answer\">David:</h3>\r\nWe are be working hard to expand our in-house factory. We named the factory, Brooklyn Sewn and it has been an amazing and rewarding experience. We are also trying to get back to our roots with more avant garde work to balance the more contemporary work we have been producing lately - the trick is finding the balance between both worlds.\r\n<h3 class=\"question\">Asher:</h3>\r\nThe KDU is growing daily with new designers, can you tell us about them?\r\n<h3 class=\"answer\">David:</h3>\r\nEach designer, artists or creative professional is hand selected by me personally. People are recommended from other members and colleagues, but the ultimate selection process is determined by me alone. I want the KDU to continue to stand in opposition to mass, technology driven platform and crowd sourcing collectives - the only way to truly avoid this is to know each member personally, having an intimate understanding of their portfolios, work styles and flow.','Oliver Cartwright','','publish','closed','closed','','oliver-cartwright','','','2012-04-05 13:21:23','2012-04-05 20:21:23','',0,'http://spiraldesign.ca/?post_type=interview&#038;p=104',0,'interview','',0),(105,1,'2012-03-05 03:57:45','2012-03-05 03:57:45','','watch','','inherit','open','open','','watch','','','2012-03-05 03:57:45','2012-03-05 03:57:45','',15,'http://spiraldesign.ca/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/watch.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(106,1,'2012-03-04 05:46:09','2012-03-04 05:46:09','MONTREAL -- <a href=\"http://tsn.ca/nhl/teams/players/?name=mikhail+grabovski\">MikhailÂ Grabovski</a> scored twice in the third period as the Toronto Maple Leafs gave new coach Randy Carlyle a victory with a 3-1 win over the Montreal Canadiens on Saturday night.\r\n\r\nThe win, only the second in the last 12 games for the slumping Leafs, ended a six-game winless run.<!--more-->\r\n\r\nThe Leafs fired fourth-year coach Ron Wilson on Friday night and hired Carlyle in a bid to energize a 12th place team for a late run to make the playoffs.\r\n\r\nHis first game behind the bench came in a nationally televised encounter between the NHL\'s oldest rivals, with a large contingent of Toronto fans in the Bell Centre seats putting up competing chants with the Canadiens supporters.','GRABOVSKI SCORES TWICE AS LEAFS TOP HABS IN CARLYLE\'S DEBUT','','inherit','open','open','','15-revision-6','','','2012-03-04 05:46:09','2012-03-04 05:46:09','',15,'http://spiraldesign.ca/15-revision-6/',0,'revision','',0),(107,1,'2012-03-04 05:48:28','2012-03-04 05:48:28','MONTREAL -- <a href=\"http://tsn.ca/nhl/teams/players/?name=mikhail+grabovski\">MikhailÂ Grabovski</a> scored twice in the third period as the Toronto Maple Leafs gave new coach Randy Carlyle a victory with a 3-1 win over the 